Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the Limpopo Provincial Economic Summit which aims to improve economic diversification in the province. JOHANNESBURG Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has arrived in Polokwane this morning where he will address the Limpopo Provincial Economic Summit.The event is aimed at bringing together various government departments, state-owned entities and the business sector to discuss ways to improve economic diversification. Ramaphosa is being accompanied by Limpopo Premier Stan Mathabatha and MECs from the province.Businesses and governments leaders gathered will try find ways to emancipate the economy of the province and ultimately the country.Ramaphosa is expected to deliver give the keynote address soon shortly.(Edited by Leeto M Khoza)